Name: juvenile type testicular granulosa cell tumor
Definition: A B cell deficiency that is characterized by deficiency of an immunoglobulin subtype. The clinical course and prognosis is dependent upon the severity of the selective deficiency and associated morbidity.

Name: adult type testicular granulosa cell tumor
Definition: A cervical adenosquamous carcinoma that is a rare form and is composed of cells with a glass-like cytoplasm.
Synonym: mixed Choriocarcinoma and Seminoma of testis
